  "prompt": "How do you know I'd your pregnant?",
  "response": "Determining if you're pregnant typically involves several steps and methods:\n\n1. **Missed Period:** One of the most common signs of pregnancy is a missed menstrual cycle. If your period is late and you've been sexually active, it could be an indication.\n\n2. **Pregnancy Tests:** The most reliable way to determine pregnancy is by using a home pregnancy test, which detects the presence of the hormone human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG) in your urine. These tests are available over-the-counter at pharmacies.\n\n3. **Symptoms:** Early signs of pregnancy can include nausea, vomiting (morning sickness), breast tenderness, increased urination, fatigue, and abdominal bloating.\n\n4. **Medical Confirmation:** For the most accurate results, visit a healthcare provider. They can perform a blood test to measure hCG levels or an ultrasound to confirm pregnancy.\n\nIf you suspect you might be pregnant, it\u2019s important to follow up with a healthcare professional for proper guidance and care.",
